8ï¸âƒ£ JavaScript Module System
What is a Module?

A portion of code

Each .js file is a module

Makes app:

Lightweight

Reusable

Organized

Example:
home.js  â†’ Home Module
index.js â†’ Index Module

Module Contains:

Variables

Functions

Classes

âŒ Members are not accessible outside
âœ” Must use export

9ï¸âƒ£ Types of JS Module Systems

CommonJS

ES Module (ESM) âœ… (Used in React)

UMD

AMD

ğŸ”Ÿ Export in ES Modules
Named Export
export var title = "Welcome";

export function login() {}

export class User {}

Default Export
var title = "Welcome";
export default title;


âœ” Only one default export per module

1ï¸âƒ£1ï¸âƒ£ Import in ES Modules
Import Named Members
import { title, login } from "./home.js";

Import Default Export
import title from "./home.js";

Invalid
import { title } from "./home.js"; // âŒ if title is default export

1ï¸âƒ£2ï¸âƒ£ Import All Members (Aliasing)
import * as aliasName from "./home.js";

aliasName.title;
aliasName.login();
aliasName.User;


âœ” Solves name conflicts
âœ” Useful when importing from multiple modules

1ï¸âƒ£3ï¸âƒ£ Handling Name Conflicts
